<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,692,828]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,765,791]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the thorn-like apophyses at the embolus of the male 
<typeStatus box="[1258,1356,765,791]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species (Latin adjective “tribulosus” meaning “thorny”); adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
