<subSubSection lastPageId="97" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,1850,2021]" lastBlockId="97.[151,1437,153,1439]" lastPageId="97" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1850,1877]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males distinguished from those of all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1850" box="[819,940,1851,1877]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Corythalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[819,940,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Corythalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following characters in combination: embolus (E) quite strong, with two conspicuous apophyses centrally (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1149,1887,1913]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Figs 47A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1161,1210,1887,1914]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[158,1430,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 67. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: A Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida. B Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: C Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia grata: D Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: Paratypes E SMNK-ARA 02232, F SMNK-ARA 02236, G SMNK-ARA 02237-1 and H SMNK-ARA 02237-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: I Male M-2 from Amazonas and J M-4 from Paraná, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927523/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">67A</figureCitation>
) which are crossing in retrolateral view (
<figureCitation box="[382,490,1923,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Figs 47B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[502,549,1923,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 70" captionStartId="131.[151,250,1560,1585]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@131.[157,1431,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="131" captionText="FIGURE 70. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, retrolateral view. Corythalia hadzji: A Lectotype from Upper Demerara-Berbice, Guyana. Corythalia trochophora Bayer, sp. nov.: B Holotype from Tungurahua, Ecuador. Corythalia lineata Bayer, sp. nov.: C Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia hamulifera Bayer, sp. nov.: D Holotype from south-eastern part of Ecuador. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: E Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida: F Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: G Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: H Paratype SMNK-ARA 02236 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia grata: I Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: J Male M-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927531/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">70E</figureCitation>
) and distally with retrolatero-distal, relatively long and very narrow extension with tip having (disto-) retrolateral orientation (
<figureCitation box="[675,759,1959,1985]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Figs 47</figureCitation>
A–B, 67A) and prolatero-distally with stout, conical and very small process; distal margin of base of E (EB) in ventral view almost reaching distal margin of tegulum (T) (gap &lt;width of RTA in ventral view) (
<figureCitation box="[501,609,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[620,673,153,180]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[158,1430,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 67. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: A Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida. B Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: C Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia grata: D Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: Paratypes E SMNK-ARA 02232, F SMNK-ARA 02236, G SMNK-ARA 02237-1 and H SMNK-ARA 02237-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: I Male M-2 from Amazonas and J M-4 from Paraná, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927523/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">67A</figureCitation>
); RTA medium-sized (shorter than width of T), without dorsal serration and with tip distinctly bent ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[624,727,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 47B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="97.[151,1437,153,1439]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,224,251]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Description. Male:</emphasis>
total length 5.6, carapace length 2.5, maximal carapace width 1.9, width of eye rectangle 1.7, opisthosoma length 2.6, opisthosoma width 1.5, fovea length 0.28. EYES: AME 0.58, ALE 0.36, PME 0.08, PLE 0.33, AME–AME 0.03, AME–ALE 0.03, PME–PME 1.46, PME–PLE 0.22, ALE–PLE 0.61, PLE–PLE 1.19, clypeus height at AME 0.29, clypeus height at ALE 0.62. Cheliceral furrow with 2 (one of them slightly smaller, both located directly next to each other) promarginal and 1 retromarginal teeth. SPINATION: palp without spines. Legs: femur 
<date box="[299,376,404,431]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="1500-01">I 1500</date>
, 
<date box="[390,480,404,431]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="1500-02">II 1500</date>
{1600}, 
<date box="[573,669,404,431]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="1500-03">III 1500</date>
, 
<date box="[682,780,405,431]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="1600-04">IV 1600</date>
; patella 
<date box="[878,955,405,431]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="1000-01">I 1000</date>
, II–IV 1010; tibia 
<date box="[1172,1250,405,432]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="1003-01">I 1003</date>
{2004}, II 3013, III–IV 3133; metatarsus 
<date box="[438,517,441,467]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="2014-01">I 2014</date>
, 
<date box="[532,620,441,467]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="2024-02">II 2024</date>
, III 3134, IV 4143{4144}. MEASUREMENT OF PALP AND LEGS: palp 2.0 [0.8, 0.3, 0.2, 0.7], I 4.4 [1.5, 0.7, 0.9, 0.8, 0.5], II 4.6 [1.5, 0.7, 1.0, 0.9, 0.5], III 5.9 [1.9, 0.8, 1.3, 1.3, 0.6], IV 6.0 [1.8, 0.8, 1.3, 1.5, 0.6]. LEG FORMULA: 4321. COPULATORY ORGAN: embolus (E) (actual tubular section) moderately long [slightly shorter than width of tegulum (T)], quite broad [centrally (even without apophyses) slightly broader than RTA in ventral view], retrolatero-distally with quite long, light and very narrow extension with tip having (disto-) retrolateral orientation (
<figureCitation box="[688,797,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[808,858,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[158,1430,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 67. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: A Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida. B Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: C Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia grata: D Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: Paratypes E SMNK-ARA 02232, F SMNK-ARA 02236, G SMNK-ARA 02237-1 and H SMNK-ARA 02237-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: I Male M-2 from Amazonas and J M-4 from Paraná, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927523/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">67A</figureCitation>
) and prolatero-distally with stout, conical and very small process, centrally with thorn-shaped apophysis prolaterally and quite prominent and pointed apophysis retrolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[258,367,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[379,432,693,720]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[158,1430,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 67. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: A Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida. B Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: C Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia grata: D Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: Paratypes E SMNK-ARA 02232, F SMNK-ARA 02236, G SMNK-ARA 02237-1 and H SMNK-ARA 02237-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: I Male M-2 from Amazonas and J M-4 from Paraná, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927523/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">67A</figureCitation>
); width of embolus base (EB) circle&gt; 1/2, but &lt;2/3 the width of T; EB located centrally to prolatero-centrally at distal part of T; T narrower than cymbium (
<figureCitation box="[933,1044,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1057,1110,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[158,1430,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 67. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: A Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida. B Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: C Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia grata: D Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: Paratypes E SMNK-ARA 02232, F SMNK-ARA 02236, G SMNK-ARA 02237-1 and H SMNK-ARA 02237-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: I Male M-2 from Amazonas and J M-4 from Paraná, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927523/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">67A</figureCitation>
); sperm duct double-stacked S-shaped, occupying more than 2/3 of T from retrolateral; proximal tegulum lobe not recognisable as such, but T proximally moderately converging and proximal ending (very) broad rounded; cymbium in ventral view distally conically converging, at distalmost section rounded; palpal tibia short, broader than long (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1252,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47</figureCitation>
A–B, 67A, 70E) and ventral tibial bump in ventral view broad, distally almost truncated, located in proximal section of prolateral half of palpal tibia and having prolatero-distal orientation; RTA in ventral view quite narrow, medium-sized, with almost distal direction and without dorsal serration (
<figureCitation box="[711,818,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[829,880,945,972]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1567,1592]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[158,1430,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 67. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, ventral view. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: A Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida. B Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: C Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia grata: D Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: Paratypes E SMNK-ARA 02232, F SMNK-ARA 02236, G SMNK-ARA 02237-1 and H SMNK-ARA 02237-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: I Male M-2 from Amazonas and J M-4 from Paraná, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927523/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">67A</figureCitation>
), in retrolateral view RTA distally converging and with tip clearly bent ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[503,611,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="96.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[312,1276,849,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[312,1276,849,1719]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 47. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov., male holotype from Departamento de Putumayo, Colombia. A–B Left palp (A ventral view; B retrolateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927481/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 47B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[623,673,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 70" captionStartId="131.[151,250,1560,1585]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,182,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@131.[157,1431,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="131" captionText="FIGURE 70. Corythalia spp., photographic images of left palps of male specimens, retrolateral view. Corythalia hadzji: A Lectotype from Upper Demerara-Berbice, Guyana. Corythalia trochophora Bayer, sp. nov.: B Holotype from Tungurahua, Ecuador. Corythalia lineata Bayer, sp. nov.: C Holotype from East Berbice-Corentyne, Guyana. Corythalia hamulifera Bayer, sp. nov.: D Holotype from south-eastern part of Ecuador. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: E Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida: F Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: G Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: H Paratype SMNK-ARA 02236 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia grata: I Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: J Male M-2 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia opima: K Lectotype from eastern part of Guatemala. Corythalia spiralis: L Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927531/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">70E</figureCitation>
). COLOURATION: see genus description for conservative aspects. Carapace red-brown, proximal sections of lateral margins without broad bands of dense, light scale hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1424,1017,1044]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="120.[151,250,1646,1671]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,526,1619]" captionTargetId="figure@120.[160,1427,525,1621]" captionTargetPageId="120" captionText="FIGURE 60. Corythalia spp., photographic images of male specimens, dorsal view. Corythalia hamulifera Bayer, sp. nov.: A Holotype from south-eastern part of Ecuador. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: B Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida: C Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: D Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: E Paratype SMNK-ARA 02236 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia grata F Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: G Male M-1 from Borba, Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia opima: H Male SMF 8437 from La Paz, El Salvador. Corythalia spiralis: I Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927509/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 60B</figureCitation>
). Legs brown to red-brown, except for proximalmost articles, patellae and tarsi being lighter (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1270,1053,1080]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="120.[151,250,1646,1671]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,526,1619]" captionTargetId="figure@120.[160,1427,525,1621]" captionTargetPageId="120" captionText="FIGURE 60. Corythalia spp., photographic images of male specimens, dorsal view. Corythalia hamulifera Bayer, sp. nov.: A Holotype from south-eastern part of Ecuador. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: B Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida: C Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: D Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: E Paratype SMNK-ARA 02236 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia grata F Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: G Male M-1 from Borba, Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia opima: H Male SMF 8437 from La Paz, El Salvador. Corythalia spiralis: I Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927509/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 60B</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma like noted in genus description under general dorsal colouration, however central transversal band very narrow (just as narrow as posterior band) and quite even and straight, chevron-like patch in central band missing; posterior band distinctly separated medially (
<figureCitation box="[488,591,1161,1188]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="120.[151,250,1646,1671]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,526,1619]" captionTargetId="figure@120.[160,1427,525,1621]" captionTargetPageId="120" captionText="FIGURE 60. Corythalia spp., photographic images of male specimens, dorsal view. Corythalia hamulifera Bayer, sp. nov.: A Holotype from south-eastern part of Ecuador. Corythalia tribulosa sp. nov.: B Holotype from Putumayo, Colombia. Corythalia valida: C Lectotype from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia flagrans sp. nov.: D Holotype from Acre, Brazil. Corythalia fragilis sp. nov.: E Paratype SMNK-ARA 02236 from Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia grata F Lectotype from São Paulo, Brazil. Corythalia vervloeti: G Male M-1 from Borba, Amazonas, Brazil. Corythalia opima: H Male SMF 8437 from La Paz, El Salvador. Corythalia spiralis: I Lectotype from Chiriquí, Panama." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3927509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3927509/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 60B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
